<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217121>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34 – 36. Facial aspect (34), lateral aspect (35), tegmen in widest aspect (36) of Lepyronoxia. A, O. irregularis sp. nov.; B, O. frontalis (Stål); C, O. boliviana sp. nov.; D, O. obliqua (Jacobi), male; E, O. quadrimaculata (Lallemand); F, O. rana (Walker); G, O. decorata sp. nov.; H, O. oculata sp. nov.; J, O. sphaerata sp. nov.; K, O. subfasciata (A. & S.); L, O. obscurata (A. & S.), male; M, O. bufo (Walker). Scale line: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217115>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. New World Orthoraphini: habitus (A – B), hind wing (C – F) including detail of hamuli on costal margin (G – H), male abdomen in ventral aspect (J) and male genital capsule in lateral aspect (K). A, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) frontalis (Stål); B, F, H, O. cassidioides Westwood, female; C, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) obliqua (Jacobi); D, Orthorapha (Balsania) concinna (Stål); E, G, Orthorapha (Balsania) geminata (Jacobi); J, K, Orthorapha (Lepyronoxia) bufo (Walker)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217115/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217116>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.217120>
    dc:description "FIGURE 33. Lateral aspect of the nominate subgenus of Orthorapha (A – E) and subgenus Balsania (F – L). A – B, color varieties of O. laeta Jacobi; C, O. cassidioides Westwood, male; D, same, female; E, O. invidia sp. nov.; F, O. inflata sp. nov.; G, O. concinna (Stål); H, O. geminata (Jacobi); J, O. sagittata sp. nov.; K, O. reducta Walker; L, O. testacea Walker. Scale line: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/217120/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

